# EvairSIM Flutter App — Project Overview

## Product Scope (AS OF April 19, 2026 pivot)

The Flutter app is a **SIM management + top-up tool**, NOT an eSIM marketplace.

### Primary feature — PCCW physical SIM
1. Customer buys PCCW physical SIM from Amazon / Temu / Jordan's website (NOT in-app)
2. Customer opens app → 3-step wizard (Scan barcode → Confirm → Done) binds the ICCID to their account
3. Customer sees SIM status, usage, expiry in My SIMs
4. Customer tops up the SIM using admin-portal-managed recharge packages

### Secondary feature — Red Tea eSIM
1. Customer receives a Red Tea eSIM activation code via email or admin push
2. Customer opens app → "Connect eSIM" → pastes LPA code (or scans QR)
3. App registers the eSIM to the account and shows install QR / status
4. Customer tops up via admin-portal-managed recharge packages

### Explicitly OUT of scope (April 2026)
- ❌ **eSIM marketplace / "Shop by country"** (was called "eCard" in H5) — customers do NOT buy new eSIMs from within the app
- ❌ **Shipping / physical SIM purchase** — no address forms, no checkout for hardware. Future: deep-link to Jordan's Amazon listing.
- ❌ **Hot packages carousel**, popular-country promos, marketing hero unrelated to PCCW / Red Tea top-up

### UI layout principle
Follow the existing H5 layout exactly, but **swap where "eCard (Red Tea)" appeared with "SIM card (PCCW)"**, and replace "eSIM country browse" surfaces with "eSIM Connect" surfaces. The top SIM Card / eSIM segmented toggle stays.

## Tech Stack
- Flutter 3.38 + Dart 3.x, Material 3
- Riverpod 2 (hooks_riverpod) + flutter_hooks (no `setState` for global state)
- GoRouter (StatefulShellRoute for bottom nav)
- Dio + `Either<Failure, T>` (fpdart) for every repository method
- Freezed + json_serializable + build_runner
- Hive + flutter_secure_storage (tokens, locale)
- qr_flutter for QR rendering

## Architecture (Clean)
- `lib/domain/` — entities + repository interfaces (pure Dart)
- `lib/data/` — Dio APIs + repository impls (depends on domain)
- `lib/presentation/` — pages, widgets, Riverpod providers, controllers
- `lib/core/` — theme, i18n, router, network, error, constants

Never import presentation from data/domain. Never import data from domain.

## Backend API base
`https://evair.zhhwxt.cn/api` — the client adds the `/v1/...` prefix per-endpoint.

### Endpoints we consume (customer side)
Auth (`/v1/h5/auth/*`):
- login / register / profile / password

SIMs (`/v1/h5/user/*` + `/v1/h5/esim/*`):
- `GET /v1/h5/user/sims` · `POST /v1/h5/user/sims/bind` · `POST /v1/h5/user/sims/unbind`
- `GET /v1/h5/esim/{iccid}` · `.../usage` · `.../enable`

Top-up (admin-managed, preferred): `/v1/app/*` with `auth:app` (our token works on both `auth:app` and `auth:h5`):
- `GET /v1/app/recharge-packages` — packages surfaced by admin portal 充值套餐管理
- `POST /v1/app/recharge` — create recharge order for a SIM
- `POST /v1/app/recharge/{id}/pay` — pay
- `GET /v1/app/recharge-records` · `/recharge-records/{id}`

Orders: `/v1/h5/orders/*` (eSIM purchase endpoint exists but we don't use it for new eSIMs anymore)

Notifications (Inbox): `GET /v1/h5/notifications` (public, admin-managed 通知管理)

Live chat (Contact Us): `auth:h5`
- `POST /v1/h5/conversations` · `POST /v1/h5/conversations/{id}/messages` · `GET /v1/h5/conversations/{id}/messages?since=`

Email: `/v1/h5/email/esim-delivery` etc.

